</p>
<p>If we run <code>behat</code> now:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">$ ./vendor/bin/behat</div></code></pre>
<p>It should run all of our features: the ls <em>and</em> web stuff. It does, and it works!
Ignore the undefined functions - those are from <code>product_admin.feature</code>: we haven't
finished that yet.</p>
<h2 id="multiple-suites">Multiple Suites <a class="headerlink" href="suites#multiple-suites" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>But we can go further. in <code>behat.yml</code>, check out the <code>suites</code> key. Currently, we
have one "suite" called <code>default</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="89371b96d7">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-13" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </span>
            
            13 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="behat.yml">behat.yml</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="1"></td>
