            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-expandable" data-range="12-18" data-last="1">
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v js-icon-load-more" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show Lines" data-placement="left"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </td>
            <td class="gap-line">
                                                    ... lines 12 - 18
                            </td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>Now, if you run the <code>default</code> suite:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">$ ./vendor/bin/behat</div></code></pre>
<p>Behat knows to only execute the features in the <code>web/</code> directory. With <code>--suite=commands</code>,
it <em>only</em> runs the features inside of <code>commands/</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">$ ./vendor/bin/behat --suite=commands</div></code></pre>
<p>So if you have two very different things that are being tested, consider separating
them into different suites entirely. But at the very least, use multiple contexts to
keep organized and stay sane.</p>

    
